#tbt to pulling 948lbs/430kg in Moscow! Can't belive this was over 4 years ago! 
This was the first meet I broke the 2k total barrier.

#tbt  so one this one time I got to workout with the @texastech_fb football team! 
I posed as a "new recruit" from out of state. Everyone was a little surprised when we started lifting 😅 
Probably one of the coolest things I've gotten to do. 
@rustywhitt was the strength and conditioning coach at the time and got it all set up. Huge thanks to him!
2nd week of sumo in a very long time. We will see how it goes for a bit!

240kg/529lbs for some easy 5s today. 
Only doing these every other week. Ive been making small jumps each time and so far so good 👍 
.
Also, this song is crazy

573lb for a few 5s. 
This is the most I've done since July! So far so good. Technique has been feeling very comfortable as well.

Episode Five: Cailer Woolam 
•
One of the greatest deadlifters of all time. Video games. Sponsorships. Brunch. And so much more.

Link in bio and streaming on all major platforms.

601lbs x 5. That went well. 
This is the most I've done in the last 8 months, since my lat tear. I was excited to lift something that started with a 6.

"Evidence indicates that it's stature, 
Merceless like a terrorist hard to capture" 🔥

Crazy pull from @swoleleell at the THSPA state meet last weekend. He also squatted 710lb and benched 385lb. That set a new state record Deadlift and Total! This is one of the craziest HS performances you'll ever see. He lives in my hometown and goes to the same high-school I did, so I had to share this! 
Kids are crazy these days 😅

507lbs x 5. Deficit stiff leg DL with slow-ish eccentric. 
.

Just wanted to share how things are going! 
There's always something that flares up and makes me have to start over wherever I'm at with training. 
Happy to say I have found a variation that feels good to do and seems to also help the areas that have been nagging. 
Over the last 2 months I've built this up week to week. I started with 155lbs and now I'm here!

540lbs x 4. Stiff leg deficit DL. 
Was gonna do 5 but then I was too dizzy after 4 😅 
I've carefully progressed these every week up to this point. Just need this to continue for a bit and I might actually be able to get somewhere! 
Pulling slow off the floor, making it more of a "peel" than a rip. 
I do look forward to getting back to normal variations after I'm finished up with this one! 
.
I always get a ton of support in the comments and my DMs about my recovery and whatnot.  I really appreciate everyone who's reached out. It really helps me keep going. Just so you guys know ❤️

Photo dump from the first 2 days of seminars here in China! 
I'm a bit lost for words as to what to say regarding how amazing this trip has already been. I still can't believe I'm here right now getting this opportunity! 
3 more cities to go. Beijing is up next 🇨🇳🔥💪

300kg for a careful single
Most I've done in 1 year, since the 2nd lat tear last July. 
Just wanted to do a little something at this cool deadlift party that went down yesterday after the seminar! 
Safe to say that China brings the hype like no other place 🔥 
We all had a blast hanging out and lifting together!
.
I've been feeling really strong lately. And this was a very easy lift, happy to say. My body still needs a little more time before I do anything like this again though. But things are headed in the right direction. Patience will pay off always!

I ❤️ U China 🇨🇳 
Really enjoyed my 2nd visit in this country. And I can not wait until the 3rd time! 
Thanks for everything.

"What got you into Lifting?" Is one of the most frequently asked questions for anyone who does any kind of physical training. 
This is my answer! 
What was it for you that made you get started? 
This was an awesome little edit the guys in china made from one of my interviews I did while I was there.

Squats and deads from the last 2 weeks!
-Low bar SQ 
- conventional DL 
- zombie front SQ 
- snatch grip deficit DL

#tbt pulling 705lbs mixed grip on an axle bar! 6ish years ago I think. 
The grip was definitely the challenge here. Also seems like a good way to tear a bicep😅 for some reason I went through a phase where I really wanted to be able to pull over 700 on the axle without straps.

Cant believe this was 6 years ago! Boss of bosses 4. 
Attempts shown are 860, 909, 927lbs  @211lbs BW 
This was my first big meet I ever got invited too. Ended up breaking the 220lb/100kg class all time deadlift world record on my 2nd and 3rd attempt! 
Had a fun battle with @belkin_one_power as well. He broke the record on his 2nd attempt with 926lbs. So I went 927lbs on my 3rd to beat that. He ended up missing 948lbs on his 3rd and I walked away with the record on that day. That was a crazy moment! 
The talent pool in powerlifting has gotten crazy over these recent years. 
At the time, this was the heaviest deadlift ever done by an American in a powerlifting meet. Regardless of weight class. 
This also made me the lightest person to ever deadlift over 900lbs!

Hey Guys. Welcome to First Law powerlifting. (@firstlaw.powerlifting ) This page is ran by me, Cailer Woolam, and is dedicated to sharing highlights and PRs from my online clients!
.
.
I've been personal training/ coaching athletes for over 6 years now. I've been very fortunate to work with so many amazing athletes. I'm always doing what I can to learn more and better myself as a coach. Ive spent years doing everything I can from a very young age to become the strongest version of myself. 
As fun as it has been to achieve my own success within the sport, I have found that helping others achieve their strength goals is even more enjoyable. 
If you have been stuck in training and are in need of some guidance or you're  just looking fot a change, feel free to reach out! 
Send me a DM to this page or my main page @doctor.deadlift for more information!

#tbt the most weight I've missed/gotten while lifting solo. 
Just reminding everyone to not use clips when you bench alone. It could save you a lot of hassle and perhaps even your life 😅👍

Big shoutout to one of my good friends @jeremyavilla for his recent deadlift PR. He finally broke the 900 barrier with this 903lbs pull!
 I've been hearing him talk about pulling this ever since I met him 7 years ago. He's been through countless setbacks since then but he never lost sight of this goal. Really pumped to see him recover and finally be able to hit this. 🙌
